cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: just off the coast of southwest Florida
cyclone.trajectory: moving west-northwest away from South Florida into the southeastern Gulf of Mexico, then forecast to slow and curl northward toward the Florida Big Bend/Panhandle late week
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Big Bend or eastern Panhandle coast

weather_observation.watch_coast: None in the United States (Cuba only)
weather_observation.warning_coast: Florida coast from the Brevard/Volusia County line south-westward around the peninsula to Anna Maria Island, including Port Canaveral
weather_observation.impacted_coast: South and central Florida peninsula including the Florida Keys and east-central Atlantic coast
weather_observation.rain_fall_above_4_inch: Unlikely (forecast totals generally 2–4 inches for east-central FL)
weather_observation.wind: Tropical-storm-force winds (35–45 mph with higher gusts) possible through Monday as outer bands cross east-central Florida
weather_observation.storm_surge: Minor inundation 1–2 ft above ground possible at high tide; highest south of the port
weather_observation.rainfall: Bands of heavy rain could deliver 2–4 inches with locally higher pockets causing brief ponding and drainage issues
weather_observation.other_hazards: Dangerous surf and rip currents; isolated tornadoes in rain bands
